# Copy to .github directory
mkdir -p .github
cp docs/COPILOT_VUE2_TO_VUE3_UPGRADE_INSTRUCTIONS.md .github/copilot-instructions.md

Option 3: Reference in Chat
When asking GitHub Copilot for help, say:

"Follow the migration guide in COPILOT_VUE2_TO_VUE3_UPGRADE_INSTRUCTIONS.md to upgrade this project from Vue 2 to Vue 3"




Upgrade this project from Vue 2 to Vue 3, migrate from bootstrap-vue to taiwindcss. Refer the docs and todo list below:

Updated all core dependencies (Vue, Router, State Management) that can run npm install only do not allow to run npm install -f or npm install --legacy-peer-deps
Migrated from Webpack to Vite build tool
Converted Vuex store to Pinia
Updated Vue Router from v3 to v4
Fixed global API changes (createApp instead of new Vue)
Updated component lifecycle hooks
Migrated environment variables (process.env → import.meta.env)
Fixed Sass deprecation warnings (@import → @use)
Installed and configured Font Awesome icons
Removed Vue 2 filters (replaced with methods/composables)
Created useFormatters composable for currency/date formatting
Migrated from Vuex (this.$store) to Pinia (useAuthStore) replace new syntax in all components.
Migrate all the components from to new syntax for vue 3
Migrate component that using vue-bootstrap to taiwinds css
Update toast notification following the guide in docs
Update sidebar following the guide and keep the style
Testing run without error
For each todo list above try to refer in copilo.github/t-instructions.md or docs/*.md

Then create document to tracking below:
MIGRATION_COMPLETE_SUMMARY.md - Complete overview
MIGRATION_STATUS.md - Component migration guide
INSTALLATION_AND_NEXT_STEPS.md - Setup instructions
MIGRATION_CHECKLIST.md - Detailed checklist
README_MIGRATION.md - Quick start guide
